TypeScript recommended, modular separation: UI / content-script / background / worker pool / profile store.

Storage: chrome.storage.sync for settings, IndexedDB for large queues/temporary data.

Workers: use Web Workers for hashing/CPU-heavy tasks.

Testing: headless Chromium integration tests for real pages; unit tests for selector heuristics, mask parser, queue logic.

Security & privacy: no credentials; local-only default; request minimal permissions and explain them in onboarding. Warn about copyright/ToS.

